    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-11-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-11-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="520"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                <head>520. <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Executive Committee record of
                    action, November 12<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d520fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KNS_1">Khrushchev</persName>’s reply to <persName
                            corresp="#p_KJF_1">Kennedy</persName> November 6 letter; safeguards
                        against offensive weapons in Cuba; aerial reconnaissance missions for
                        November 13. Top Secret. 1 p. Kennedy Library, NFS, Meetings and Memoranda
                        Series, Executive Committee Meetings, Vol. II, Meetings 25–32A.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <idno type="document-identifier">Meeting No. 25</idno>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-11-12T17:00:00">November 12, 1962, 5
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d520-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d520-1"/>
                <p>1. Mr. Bundy summarized Chairman <persName corresp="#p_KNS_1"
                        >Khrushchev</persName>’s reply to the President’s message of November 6th.
                    Following a discussion, the Pres<pb facs="1574" n="1399" type="typeset"
                        xml:id="pg_1399"/>ident authorized the dispatch of an interim response
                    dealing with the removal of the <gloss target="#t_IL28_1">IL–28</gloss>
                    bombers.</p>
                <p>2. The President requested further study and recommendations as to courses of
                    action with respect to safeguards against offensive weapons in Cuba and
                    conditions in which we should and should not give an assurance against
                    invasion.</p>
                <p>3. The President authorized tomorrow’s aerial reconnaissance missions comprising
                    up to five <gloss target="#t_U2_1">U–2</gloss> flights and ten low-level
                    sorties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_BM_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BM_1">McGeorge Bundy</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
